Replicasets

-> Replicasets ensures a specified number of Pod replicas are running at any given time.
-> It creates or deletes pods if needed.


Deployments

-> It provide declarative updates for Pods and Replicasets with rollback capabilities.
-> Features:
    - Rolling updates
    - Rollback to previous versions
    - Pause and resume deployments
    - Version history tracking


Deployment Lifecycle

-> Pod lifecycle

    - Pending (Pod is pending until its containers started)
        |
    - Running (At least one container is running in the Pod)
        |
    - Failed (one or more containers exited with non-zero status) | Succeded (All containers in the POd terminated successfully)

    - Unknown (when state of the Pod cannot be determined)


